@ZyX-I lets be real, who doesn't use public key based ssh in 2016? 

With the escape sequences approach, wouldn't more code have to be implemented though? This is literally only 1 line in ~/.zshrc and 2 lines in ~/.ssh/config and a tiny little script. Its not that complicated. As for determining the host you're right, I'm not sure. Perhaps a option on the command line. 

But I guess the escape sequences are a much more clean way to handle this. If I wanted to implement the escape sequences, which files should I poke around with?
